        <body>
            <pb n="3" facs="#f0001"/>
            <dateline>
                <hi rendition="#et">
                    <hi rendition="#k">London,</hi> Oct. 17.</hi>
            </dateline>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Extent and Population of America.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The following estimate of the extent, in<lb break="yes"/>square leagues, and
                    population, of the Conti-<lb break="no"/>nent of America in 1822, was lately
                        transmit-<lb break="no"/>ted by Baron de Humboldt from Paris, to<lb
                        break="yes"/>President Bolivar, with the accompanying<lb break="yes"
                    />letter:&#x2014;</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Square Leagues.</hi></cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Population.</hi></cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Mexico, or New Spain</cell>
                        <cell>75,830</cell>
                        <cell>6,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Guatemala</cell>
                        <cell>16,740</cell>
                        <cell>1,600,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Cuba and Puerto Rico</cell>
                        <cell>4,430</cell>
                        <cell>800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell rows="3">Colombia <list rendition="#leftBraced">
                                <item>Venezuela</item>
                                <item>New Granada</item>
                            </list></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>33,700</cell>
                        <cell>900,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>58,250</cell>
                        <cell>1,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Peru</cell>
                        <cell>42,150</cell>
                        <cell>1,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Chile</cell>
                        <cell>14,240</cell>
                        <cell>1,100,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Buenos Ayres</cell>
                        <cell>126,770</cell>
                        <cell>2,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Total, formerly Spanish</cell>
                        <cell>372,110</cell>
                        <cell>16,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   United States</cell>
                        <cell>125,440</cell>
                        <cell>10,200,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   Brazil</cell>
                        <cell>256,990</cell>
                        <cell>4,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                
                <lb break="yes"/><lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The above surfaces have been calculated<lb break="yes"/>with great care, on maps
                    rectified by astro-<lb break="no"/>nomical observations, The calculations
                        have<lb break="yes"/>been several times repeated by M. Mathieu,<lb
                        break="yes"/>Member of the Board of Longitude and of<lb break="yes"/>the
                    Institute, as well as by myself. The re-<lb break="no"/>sults differ from those
                    published in 1809, in<lb break="yes"/>the Political Essay on Mexico. Then the<lb
                        break="yes"/>inhabited parts alone had been calculated,<lb break="yes"
                    />without including the desert regions, over<lb break="yes"/>which the
                    independent tribes of the indigen-<lb break="no"/>ous inhabitants wander. Now
                    the whole ex-<lb break="no"/>tent of each country, to its furtherest limits,<lb
                        break="yes"/>has been measured.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The population of the different parts of<lb break="yes"/><hi rendition="#i">ci
                        devant</hi> Spanish America is very uncertain,<lb break="yes"/>nevertheless
                    each portion has been calcula-<lb break="no"/>ted according to the latest data
                    which have<lb break="yes"/>reached me. The present estimate ought to<lb
                        break="yes"/>be considered in the same light as all my oth-<lb break="no"
                    />er works on America; they are no other than<lb break="yes"/>essays, in which
                    every thing will have to be<lb break="yes"/>done over again. Statistical
                    calculations can<lb break="yes"/>only be rendered perfect by degrees, in like<lb
                        break="yes"/>manner as the elements of meteorological<lb break="yes"/>and
                    astronomical tables.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Comparison.</hi>&#x2014;Spain contains 16,094 square<lb
                        break="yes"/>leagues&#x2014;Europe contains 304,710 square<lb break="yes"
                    />leagues, and the whole of Southorn America<lb break="yes"/>581,891 square
                    leagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">(Signed)<lb break="yes"/>HUMBOLDT.</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
